Aji Kolomi, the 2019 ex-All Progressives Congress (APC) governorship aspirant in Yobe State has emerged as the senatorial candidate on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to represent Zone ‘A’ of the state in 2023. In the 2023 senatorial election, Kolomi will have to slug it out with ex-Yobe State Governor Ibrahim Geidam who is the incumbent Senator Representing Zone ‘A’. In Yobe, seven local government councils make up Zone ‘A’ Senatorial District namely: Damaturu, Gujba, Gulani, Tarmuwa, Bursari, Geidam and Yunusari. In other zones of the state, Halilu Mazagane has emerged winner of the primary election conducted in Potiskum town to represent Zone ‘B’ Senatorial District consisting of Potiskum, Fika, Fune and Nangere local government councils. While Zone ‘C’ which consists of Bade, Jakusko, Yusufari, Karasuwa, Nuguru and Machina elected Ilu Alhaji Bello as their senatorial candidate According to the opposition party, all the senatorial candidates on Monday emerged through consensus. The list of Senatorial Candidates as obtained by DAILY POST is as follows: 1) Zone ‘A’ :Damaturu, Gujba, Gulani, Tarmuwa, Bursari, Geidam, Yunusari LGs Candidate: Aji Kolomi 2) Zone ‘B’ : Potiskum, Fune, Fika, Nangere Candidate: Halilu Mazagane 3) Zone ‘C’ : Bade, Jakusko, Yusufari, Karasuwa, Nguru, Machina, Candidate: Ilu Alhaji Bello DAILY POST also obtained the full list of those who emerged as House Representatives candidates on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Yobe State. There are six federal constituencies across the three Senatorial Districts in the state. The list shows that all the candidates are males: 1) Nangere/Potiskum – Engineer A.A Waziri 2) Fune/Fika – Engr. Mohammed Jajere 3) Damaturu/Gujba/Gulani/Tarmuwa – Abdullahi Idrissa 4) Bade/Jakusko – Malam Hassan IBN Jaks 5) Nguru/Yusufari/Machina/Karasuwa – Mohammed Rabiu Shuaibu 6) Geidam/Yunusari/Bursari –Alhaji Hassan Tasala The list of successful candidates for the State House of Assembly is as follows: 1) Potiskum Central – Yayaji Ibrahim Na’Ibbi
